<h2 id="what-is-smartwaiver">📋 What Is Smartwaiver?</h2>

<p>Smartwaiver is a cloud-based digital waiver platform that lets tour operators create, distribute, and store liability waivers electronically. Founded in 2012, it's evolved from a simple e-signature tool into a full participant management system with kiosk mode, booking integrations, and compliance features that actually hold up in court.</p>

<p>The platform works across three main use cases: pre-arrival waivers sent via email or booking confirmation, on-site kiosk signing for walk-ins, and embedded waivers on your website. All signed documents get stored with timestamp verification, IP logging, and audit trails that insurance companies and lawyers actually accept.</p>

<p>Unlike generic e-signature tools like DocuSign or HelloSign, Smartwaiver is purpose-built for activity businesses. That means features like minor consent handling, photo capture, emergency contact collection, and the ability to process hundreds of waivers during peak check-in windows without the system choking.</p>

