<h2 id="key-features">⚙️ Key Features for Tour Operators</h2>

<h3>Customizable Waiver Builder</h3>

<p>The drag-and-drop builder handles everything from simple liability releases to complex multi-activity waivers with conditional logic. You can create different waiver versions for different activities, add custom fields for medical conditions or experience levels, and include photo/video consent sections that many operators forget until they need marketing footage.</p>

<p>Importantly, the builder doesn't require legal expertise to use, but it does support attorney review workflows. Your lawyer can access a preview link, suggest edits, and you can implement changes without starting over.</p>

<h3>Kiosk Mode</h3>

<p>The dedicated kiosk application runs on iOS and Android tablets with offline capability. Guests sign even when your wifi drops during a thunderstorm. Completed waivers sync automatically when connectivity returns. We recommend dedicated tablets for this rather than sharing with POS systems—the $300 investment prevents check-in bottlenecks that cost far more in delayed departures.</p>

<h3>Pre-Registration Links</h3>

<p>Every waiver gets a unique URL that you can embed in booking confirmations, reminder emails, or SMS messages. The link remembers partial completions, so guests who abandon mid-form can return and finish without restarting. This single feature probably saves 15+ minutes of check-in time per tour group.</p>

<h3>Minor Consent Handling</h3>

<p>Activity businesses live and die by proper minor consent documentation. Smartwaiver handles the complexity: parent/guardian signatures for minors, age verification, ability to sign for multiple minors on one form, and clear documentation showing which adult authorized which child's participation. This is table stakes for any family-oriented tour operation and an area where generic e-signature tools completely fail.</p>

<h3>Photo Capture</h3>

<p>The built-in photo capture adds participant photos to waiver records. For operations where you need to verify identity at check-in (think alcohol-involved tours or high-risk activities), this eliminates the "my friend signed for me" problem. It also helps staff match faces to waivers when managing large groups.</p>

<h3>API and Integrations</h3>

<p>The REST API is well-documented and stable. We've built custom integrations connecting Smartwaiver to homegrown booking systems, CRM platforms, and <a href="/guides/tour-operator-crm-setup">customer relationship management workflows</a> without major issues. Native integrations exist for most booking platforms, and webhook support enables real-time waiver completion notifications.</p>

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Set up webhook notifications to trigger when waivers complete. This lets front desk staff see real-time check-in status without manually refreshing the dashboard. For operations with separate booking and check-in stations, this eliminates the constant "did they sign yet?" radio chatter.
</div>

